        "answer_count": 6,
        "title": "Finding the last zero&#39;s index in an array",
        "body": "<p>I wrote the following code for finding the last zero index in an array:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Stack {\n    public static void main(String[] args){\n        int[] a=new int[5];\n        a[0]=1;\n        a[1]=0;\n        a[2]=90;\n        a[3]=0;\n        a[4]=4;\n        findLast(a);\n    }\n    public static int findLast(int[] x){\n        for(int i=0;i&lt;x.length;i++){\n         if(x[i]==0){\n             System.out.println(i);             \n         }\n        }\n        return 0;\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The output is as follows:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>1\n3\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>What I really want is the index 3.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 14657278,
        "tags": ["java"],
        "score": 1,
        "accepted_answer_id": 14657289,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 788
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4af3541c00d591e9a518b9c0b3b1190a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 134022,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 335858,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/335858/sergey-kalinichenko",
                "reputation": 729237,
                "display_name": "Sergey Kalinichenko",
                "accept_rate": 81
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 6,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1359764907,
            "creation_date": 1359764907,
            "body": "<ul>\n<li>Start at the end of the array (i.e. <code>i=x.length-1<\/code>)<\/li>\n<li>Decrement <code>i<\/code> rather than incrementing (i.e. use <code>i--<\/code>)<\/li>\n<li>Stop as soon as you reach zero (i.e. add <code>break<\/code> after <code>println<\/code>).<\/li>\n<li>Make your stopping condition such that the loop processes element at index zero.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n",
            "answer_id": 14657289,
            "question_id": 14657278
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ab3571b7038baabdee4f2d0ac1793c76?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 971933,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 994342,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/994342/bikeshedder",
                "reputation": 7547,
                "display_name": "bikeshedder"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 3,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1359764966,
            "creation_date": 1359764966,
            "body": "<p>Just reverse the loop going from <code>x.length-1<\/code> to <code>0<\/code> and return the index on first match:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static int findLast(int[] x) {\n    for (int i=x.length-1; i&gt;=0; i--) {\n        if (x[i] == 0) {\n            // match found, return index\n            return i;\n        }\n    }\n    // no match found, return invalid index\n    return -1;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 14657297,
            "question_id": 14657278
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4014335042ca36d9608a4c9cd48b01a2?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1673809,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1539741,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1539741/nbbk",
                "reputation": 1102,
                "display_name": "nbbk",
                "accept_rate": 48
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1359767718,
            "creation_date": 1359765256,
            "body": "<pre><code>public class Stack {\n    public static void main(String[] args){\n        int[] a=new int[5];\n        a[0]=1;\n        a[1]=0;\n        a[2]=90;\n        a[3]=0;\n        a[4]=4;\n        findLast(a);\n    }\n    public static void findLast(int[] x){\n        for(int i=x.length()-1;i&gt;0;i++){\n        if(x[i]==0){\n            System.out.println(i);\n            break;\n        }\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>}<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 14657346,
            "question_id": 14657278,
            "last_edit_date": 1359767718
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1bbffa7ac31beb84f5cefe5e148fbd44?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1679520,
