                "display_name": "Andrew Templeton"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1359771702,
            "creation_date": 1359771702,
            "body": "<p>Start from the END of the array and decrement through. Should we never find a zero, this returns -1, which is always outside of the index. This is interpreted by you<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Stack {\npublic static void main(String[] args){\n    int[] a=new int[5];\n    a[0]=1;\n    a[1]=0;\n    a[2]=90;\n    a[3]=0;\n    a[4]=4;\n    findLast(a);\n}\npublic static int findLast(int[] x){\n    for(int i=x.length-1;i&gt;=0;i--){\n     if(x[i]==0){\n         return i;             \n     }\n    }\n    return -1;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>}<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 14657961,
            "question_id": 14657278
        }
